Access demos, installation guides, repair instructions, and corporate data very securely. View maps, get directions, and optimise routing. Troubleshoot from the field with-real time communication. Close out work orders, capture customer signatures, and automate work streams via single device.

Touch and pen interface with line of business apps free the field worker’s hands for handling tools and test equipment. Apps from the Windows Store can be easily downloaded to help field workers manage their time, connect with colleagues, and get more out of their busy day.  Corporate functions, including field operations, can send files directly to field workers. Email and teleconferencing keep field workers in constant contact with the site managers and corporate offices.

Modern authenticators ensure that only the field worker can log into the machine, preventing lost or stolen devices from being accessed. Biometrics, Virtual SmartCards with TPM chips, and picture passwords are all available for ensuring that only the authorised user can log into their data and apps.

Reduce costs, maintain compliance, and improve IT efficiency by unifying management and security for PCs and mobile devices in a single infrastructure. System Center Configuration Manager 2012 SP1 and Windows Intune combine via a single admin console to help unify device management across a wide variety of device types.

Tailored to the field worker’s business, custom LOB apps provide connection to existing databases and software systems. Internal LOB apps provide a customised solution that fits the enterprise need, rather than purchasing unused feature sets. Works across devices so phones, tablets, and desktops all have the same experience. Field operations managers in on-site offices can use the same app from their desks as the field worker sees in the field.
